  2.Restrictions.

  When exercising the above rights, you must strictly comply with the
following restrictions. Any violation will result in immediate
termination of your license:

  a) No Commercial Use: It is strictly prohibited to use the Software
  (including its source code, binaries, modified derivative versions,
  and the built-in tools and built-in plugins contained therein) for
  any commercial purpose. This includes but is not limited to: paid
  sharing, publishing, selling, renting, sublicensing, placing it
  behind a paywall, or providing it as part of a standalone commercial
  product or service;

  b) No Closed-Source Use Without Commercial Authorization: Unless you
  have first obtained prior written commercial authorization from Team
  APE:RIP, you may not use the Software, any copied or modified
  portion of its source code, or any derivative version thereof in,
  for, or as part of any closed-source project, closed-source product,
  closed-source service, hosted deployment, internal system, or any
  other arrangement under which the relevant corresponding source code
  is not publicly disclosed in accordance with this Agreement;

  c) No Reverse Engineering: You may not reverse engineer, decompile,
  or disassemble the Software, or otherwise attempt to obtain the
  protected source code, undisclosed implementations, private
  interfaces, protocol details, or security mechanisms of the
  Software.

  3.Source Code Copying Requirements.

  If you copy parts of the Software's source code into your project and
distribute it, use it, make it available, or otherwise cause it to be
used by others, you must comply with the following:

  a) Prominent Notice: You must include a prominent notice in the
  copied source code stating which source code was copied and the date
  of copying, and clearly indicate that you copied parts of this
  project. If the project that copied this source code has a graphical
  user interface, you must display that you copied parts of this
  project and provide a way to navigate to the relevant interface of
  this project;

  b) Disclosure Obligations for Partially Open-Source or Otherwise
  Non-Fully-Open Projects: If a project that copies, modifies,
  adapts, links to, incorporates, invokes, interoperates with, or
  otherwise uses any portion of the Software's source code is only
  partially open source or is otherwise not fully open source, then
  unless prior written commercial authorization has been obtained from
  Team APE:RIP, you must publicly disclose the portions associated
  with the use of this project's source code, including the copied
  portions, modified portions, derivative portions, adaptation layers,
  interface adaptation code, linkage code, invocation code,
  interoperating code, and any build, installation, packaging,
  deployment, configuration, scripting, or other supporting materials
  necessary to enable a recipient to build, install, deploy, and
  obtain substantially the same effect as the actually distributed,
  provided, or released version;

  c) Network Service Source Disclosure: If you use, modify, deploy,
  host, or otherwise make available the Software's source code, any
  copied portion thereof, or any derivative version thereof to provide
  functionality to users over a network, including through web
  services, websites, APIs, remote invocation, hosted platforms,
  browser-accessible systems, software as a service, or any other
  remote interaction model, then unless prior written commercial
  authorization has been obtained from Team APE:RIP, you must
  prominently provide every such user with an immediate and practical
  means, free of charge, to obtain the corresponding source code of
  the running version, including the relevant associated portions and
  the build, installation, deployment, configuration, and other
  supporting materials necessary to produce substantially the same
  effect as the version actually running or otherwise made available
  to such users. This obligation applies regardless of whether the
  Software itself is distributed to those users;

  d) No Tampering with Copyright and Display Content: It is strictly
  prohibited to develop projects that remove, minimize, obscure, or
  modify Team APE:RIP copyright notices, team identifiers, or any
  notifications in the Software. It is strictly prohibited to use code
  modifications or third-party injections to obscure, remove, or
  modify any advertisements or sponsorship content displayed in the
  main interface or elsewhere; the foregoing restrictions also apply
